The paper focuses on image search and leverages both visual and textual modalities for better similarity measure with queries. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of attention mechanisms and language models, which are common in natural language processing (cs.CL) and multimedia (cs.MM) research. Finally, the paper proposes a novel learning method, which involves a hierarchy of intra and inter-attention networks, indicating that the paper may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category.
